 "components": {
  "instruction": "You are tasked with classifying user messages about banking or financial app operations into one very specific, predefined category label. Your output must adhere to the exact instructions below.\n\n**Input/Output Format:**\n- Each input consists of a JSON-style key-value pair: \"text\" (the user’s message).\n- Your output must be ONLY one label, chosen verbatim from the provided category list, with correct capitalization and no additional text or formatting.\n\n**Core Task:**\n- Read the message in the \"text\" field and assign the label that is the single, most precise, and narrowly applicable to the literal, explicit content of the message.\n- NEVER infer the user’s intention or add context that is not directly and specifically stated in the message.\n\n**Rules & Domain-Specific Guidelines:**\n- Always classify strictly according to **explicit** wording. If the message is ambiguous, choose the most specific matching option solely based on visible details.\n- **For transfer status queries:**\n    - Use “pending_transfer” only for messages asking about current transfers that are not complete and that mention timing or the fact that the transfer hasn’t arrived/finished.\n    - Use “transfer_timing” only for general questions about how long a transfer takes, never for specific in-progress or late transfers.\n- **If the balance hasn’t updated after a bank transfer (e.g., “I transferred money but the balance hasn't changed.”), ALWAYS use \"balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer\". This specifically handles scenarios where a user’s balance is not showing the transferred amount after sending money.**\n- **PIN and passcode queries:**\n    - Use \"get_physical_card\" for questions about a PIN (usually associated with a physical card).\n    - Use \"passcode_forgotten\" ONLY if the user mentions a forgotten app passcode, and NOT for card PINs.\n- **Top-Up Issues:**\n    - Use “pending_top_up” only for top-ups awaiting completion.\n    - Use “top_up_reverted” for any failed, missing, or reverted top-ups (NEVER use general \"failed\", \"pending\", or \"cancel\" for top-ups).\n    - “failed_transfer” and “cancel_transfer” are ONLY for failed or canceled TRANSFERS, NOT top-ups.\n- **Payments, Exchanges, and Receiving:**\n    - “card_payment_not_recognised” is only for disputed/unrecognized card payments.\n    - “transfer_fee_charged” and “card_payment_fee_charged” should only be used if the message explicitly mentions a fee related to the transfer or card payment, respectively.\n    - For questions about getting or using a disposable virtual card, use “get_disposable_virtual_card”.\n    - “exchange_rate” or “exchange_via_app” are only for messages explicitly about currency exchange or rates in the app.\n    - For receiving payments in another currency, if the focus is on the act of receiving, use “receiving_money” unless exchange functions are specifically mentioned.\n    - For instructions or requests to verify something, use “verify_my_identity” or “verify_source_of_funds” as directly fits the explicit mention in the message.\n    - For topping up by cash or cheque, use “top_up_by_cash_or_cheque” ONLY if this method is overtly stated.\n- **Generalization Avoidance:**\n    - Do NOT generalize; always match the most specific and directly stated label, not a broader or related category.\n- **If a message best fits a label describing a highly specific technical state (such as “balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer”), choose that over a more general status label (such as \"pending_transfer\").**\n\n**Labels:**\nChoose ONLY from this list, spelled and capitalized as provided:\nautomatic_top_up, balance_not_updated_after_bank_transfer, beneficiary_not_allowed, cancel_transfer, card_payment_fee_charged, card_payment_not_recognised, declined_cash_withdrawal, exchange_rate, exchange_via_app, failed_transfer, get_disposable_virtual_card, get_physical_card, passcode_forgotten, pending_top_up, pending_transfer, receiving_money, reverted_card_payment?, top_up_by_cash_or_cheque, top_up_reverted, topping_up_by_card, transfer_fee_charged, transfer_into_account, transfer_timing, verify_my_identity, verify_source_of_funds.\n\n**Key Principle:**  \nAlways select the most specific, domain-narrow label that fits the explicit, overt details in the message. Do not apply broader or generalized categories if a highly specific option matches.\n\n**Summary:**  \nRead only what is written, avoid assumptions, and use the most precise label from the given list according to the explicit content of the user message."
